benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/timeline - Retrieve account timeline

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios TC01 (basic 200), TC02 (parallel), TC03/04/05 (audit and combined), TC06 (no data), TC07 (large data with performance hint), TC09 (not found), TC10/TC11 (auth errors), TC12 (service unavailable), TC13 (dependent service down), TC14/TC15 (security inputs), TC16 (ignore unsupported params), TC17 (edge empty data), TC18/TC19 (max/min UUID length edge cases), TC20 (concurrency), TC21/TC22 (regressions), TC23 (backward compatibility), TC24 (accessibility), TC25 (timeout), TC26 (retry), TC27/TC28 (invalid param values)
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for pagination handling with large datasets or page-based retrieval.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache freshness.
Authorization: Tests cover 401 for missing/invalid tokens but no explicit 403 scenarios or token refresh/expiry handling.
Rate Limiting: No tests verifying behavior under rapid repeated requests or throttling.
Auditing/Logging Verification: While audit levels are requested, formal verification via logs or dedicated assertions is not consistently defined across all audit scenarios.
Edge case diversity: Several edge cases exist (TC18/TC19/student max/min UUID) but no explicit tests for boundary parsing when accountId length varies within valid UUID formats beyond max/min cases.
recommendations: Add pagination tests to verify proper paging behavior and response shape when large timelines are returned (include page size, page tokens, and total counts).
Add caching tests to validate presence and correctness of caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation behavior.
Introduce explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios to cover authorization beyond simple 401 Unauthorized (e.g., insufficient permissions).
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure the API handles bursts within defined quotas without failures.
Enhance auditing/log assertions to verify actual audit field content across all relevant scenarios (not just presence, but exact structure/values per FULL/MINIMAL).
